      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-ml-charcoal pt-6 pb-2">1. Commitment to Achieving Net Zero</h2>
      <p>Marentis Labs is committed to achieving Net Zero emissions by 2050 for our UK operations.</p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-ml-charcoal pt-6 pb-2">2. Baseline Emissions Footprint</h2>
      <p>Baseline emissions are a record of the greenhouse gases that have been produced in the past and were produced prior to the introduction of any strategies to reduce emissions. Baseline emissions are the reference point against which emissions reduction can be measured.</p>

      <p><strong>Baseline Year: 2025 (First year of incorporation)</strong></p>

      <p><strong>Additional details relating to the Baseline emissions calculations:</strong></p>
      <p>Marentis Labs was incorporated in 2025. This first reporting period serves as our baseline. Calculations follow the GHG Reporting Protocol Corporate Standard using the Operational Control approach. Our footprint is characteristic of a lean, asset-light professional services firm.</p>
      <p>To allow for institutional scaling, we have calibrated our baseline using an Intensity Metric of emissions per Full-Time Equivalent (FTE) employee. This ensures that our reduction progress is measured against operational efficiency as the firm grows.</p>

