      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-ml-charcoal pt-6 pb-2">4. Emissions Reduction Targets</h2>
      <p>Marentis Labs recognises that as a high-growth advisory firm, our absolute headcount is projected to increase. To ensure sustainable growth, we have adopted an <strong>Intensity-Based Reduction Target</strong> alongside our absolute commitment.</p>
      <p>We project that our carbon intensity will decrease from <strong>2.66 tCO<sub>2</sub>e/FTE</strong> to <strong>1.33 tCO<sub>2</sub>e/FTE</strong> by 2030. This represents a <strong>50% increase in carbon efficiency</strong> per employee.</p>
      <p>By prioritising intensity metrics, we ensure that every new associate joining Marentis Labs adheres to a progressively lower carbon threshold, ultimately reaching Net Zero (Neutralisation) by 2050.</p>

